    "title" : "EMMS Attendance and Location Monitoring API",
    "description" : "OpenAPI documentation for the Employee Management and Monitoring System (EMMS).\n\nThis specification documents the attendance and location-tracking workflow from the Employee Panel\nthrough to the Admin Panel monitoring experience. It is designed to be ready for SwaggerHub import\nand to support Swagger UI presentation.\n\nProcess overview:\n1. Employee logs in to the system.\n2. Employee opens the attendance page.\n3. Employee records attendance in strict order: Morning In, Morning Out, Afternoon In, Afternoon Out.\n4. The browser captures geolocation before attendance is submitted.\n5. The frontend sends the request to the backend API.\n6. The backend validates authentication, payload structure, coordinates, and the next valid attendance step.\n7. The system stores attendance and location data in the database.\n8. The employee can review attendance history and recent location logs.\n9. The admin monitors daily attendance and location activity from the Admin Panel.\n\nNotes:\n- Paths marked with `x-emms-implementation-status: documented-only` are included for documentation completeness\n  and SwaggerHub review even if a matching route is not yet implemented in the Django project.\n- The live Django project currently exposes `/api/attendance/record/` and `/api/attendance/location-history/`.\n- Authentication is session-based in the live web application and is documented in this specification through a secure documentation-oriented sessionAuth scheme.\n",
